ins Tomorrow, 1950), directed by Nicole Védrès and featuring Pablo Picasso and Jean-Paul Sartre, as well as the feature film High Hell (1958). He was married to Lillie Mayer (born July 29, 1889).", "biography_author": "Wikidata", "date_of_biography": "2023-08-01T14:07:17.710465+10:00", "external_links": [{"id": 3595, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Arthur_Mayer"}], "uuid": "50c148bc-1731-428c-affb-967d02373afd", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "15551", "external_references": [{"id": 25416, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q16009504"}, {"id": 27375, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "12588282"}, {"id": 27376, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n81104034"}, {"id": 27377, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n81104034"}], "date_modified": "2023-09-05T17:47:38.742897+10:00"}, {"id": 75176, "name": "Guy Furner", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2187889, "title": "Parent teacher interviews", "work_id": 71361, "role": "cinematographer", "role_id": 32, "is_primary": false}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [{"id": 9, "name": "Male", "slug": "male"}], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T15:04:01.418938+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "13806aee-de14-4be6-a3ae-24e9d80f5f28", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "37574", "external_references": [{"id": 36558, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q121126855"}], "date_modified": "2023-06-14T16:33:30.576250+10:00"}, {"id": 75175, "name": "Merill Stewart", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2187519, "title": "Pardonnez moi, Mr. Karsh", "work_id": 71358, "role": "director", "role_id": 938, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_